A radiograph (
Fig. 3
) reveals that there are 198 total vertebrae ( 186 costals and 12 caudals with 5 pairs of lymphapophyses); the costal/vertebral ratio is 1.90 : 1 . As with all Typhlopidae , the atlas and axis are devoid of ribs and the third vertebra supports the first pair of ribs.
